Changes since v7.7
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Update package requirements for Home-Assistant Core version:  2023.5.2 

* JambulaTV: Switch to using port 8507 when accessing the latest versions  of Home-Assistant Core 

* JambulaTV: Add/Remove symbolic link to Home-Assistant Core's configuration directory during installs/uninstalls 
  respectively.  The symlink  is needed by some tools that don't know about version info and  it makes life easier 
  on the command line 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Home-Assistant Core to the latest Github version:  2023.6.3 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files and split into different  directories depending on 
  Home-Assistant version used 

* JambulaTV: Fix minor bugs in the UMEME power outages via scraper tool  i.e. Update 'jambulatv-umeme-outages-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Home-Assistant Core to the latest Github version:  2023.7.1 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files for version(s):  2023.6.3 and 2023.7.1 

* JambulaTV: Add more TTS generated voice alert sound files that are used  to alert presence status of residents in 
  Home-Assistant 

* JambulaTV: Add timeout if GSM modem is not discovered in 25 seconds by  PPP/modem initialization script 
  i.e. 'jambulatv-ppp-init' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Home-Assistant Core to the latest Github version:  2023.8.2 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.253 

* JambulaTV: Add Home-Assistant configuration files for version(s):  2023.8.2 


Changes since v7.6
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Add support for displaying logo(s) of Internet radio stations  in Home-Assistant's lovelace dashboard when on-line streaming  is started i.e. Update the Internet radio streamer tool:  'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where there's no sound after upgrade/install of  Pulseaudio sound server 

* JambulaTV: Refactor our global settings file so that other programming  languages like Python can use it i.e. Escape all values of  variables specified in 'global-settings.cfg' file 

* JambulaTV: Cleanup initial and main functions file 

* JambulaTV: Rename ALSA configuration routines 'alsa_mixer_configure'  to 'alsa_mixer_volume_levels_setup' in initial and main  functions file i.e. Make ALSA configuration modular 

* JambulaTV: Update pocketsphinx language dictionary and model files 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where variables for our tools are not added to  the global settings file as is expected. See changes in  commit: 3a5fe71613ece039d01d7fa38c39c01c71821fe4 

* JambulaTV: Make gsm ussd controller tool i.e. jambulatv-gsm-ussd-ug  compatible with Home-Assistant scripts and automations 

* JambulaTV: In addition to local and global news headlines, add support  for downloading and playing news podcasts to the fetch news  via scraper tool i.e. jambulatv-fetch-news-via-scraper 

* JambulaTV: Modify command used to fetch the latest news headlines in  ASR skills i.e. Update 'jambulatv-asr-skills' tool 

* JambulaTV: Fix wind information typos in the weather via scraper tool:  'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' since it was causing a  mis-pronounciation of winds by the Text-to-Speech service 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add several TTS generated voice alert sound files that are  used by various automations and scripts in Home-Assistant 

* JambulaTV: Switch from using service to hosts in Icinga2 when discovering  WiFi access points  i.e. Remove 'Discover Wifi Access Point'  Icinga2 service as it is no longer needed.  Replace it with  newly added Icinga2 template host i.e. 'jambula-01-wifi-ap' 

* JambulaTV: Change the MQTT payload messages used when publishing the  usage states of remote PCs i.e. Use 'Home' and 'Away' in  the tool: 'jambulatv-remote-pc-usage-status' as this is  needed for the device tracker in Home-Assistant to work  as expected 

*  JambulaTV: Switch to using a different tool and skills for voice commands  i.e. Add a new tool named 'jambulatv-voice-assistant.service'  It is a replacement for the previous speech to text tool and is  written in Python 3 and supports on the fly generated skills to  translate voice commands into text 

* JambulaTV: Add support for querying mobile money balances via the GSM  USSD controller tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-gsm-ussd-ug' 

* JambulaTV: Refactor the code used in presence detection via Hostapd  i.e. Update 'jambulatv-presence-detection-via-hostapd' 

* JambulaTV: While querying for nearby WiFi devices promiscuously, do  not run command to bring UP the monitor interface if the  specified interface does not exist i.e. Update Icinga2  plugin: check_tshark.  This prevents Icinga2 from giving  false positives and reporting WifI nodes as UP 

* JambulaTV: Add TTS generated voice alert sound files that are used to  alert presence status of residents in Home-Assistant 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Change the main menu code for Airtel queries in the GSM USSD  controller tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-gsm-ussd-ug' 

* JambulaTV: Support download of source packages via a remote FTP server  during initial installation 

* JambulaTV: Remove all sounds and music files currently used by our  Asterisk server instance from the project's contribution  directory and move to an external location 

* JambulaTV: Add support for upgrading to the latest Python 3.11.x packages 

* JambulaTV: Change the directory path where requirements for Python based packages are located 

* JambulaTV: Add home streaming test video clip to project's contributed directory 

* JambulaTV: Update contributed jazz music playlist to include revised stream URLs  for Smoothjazz.com i.e. Online-Radio-Jazz.m3u 

* JambulaTV: Always update youtube-dl package when Internet status changes  to UP  i.e. Update the Internet/DNS monitoring tool:  jambulatv-dns-status-triggers 

* JambulaTV: Add support for creating Python virtual environments in order  to enable management of separate Python package installations  i.e. Allow for some Python packages to be isolated in order  to avoid breakages due to dependencies 

* JambulaTV: Add support for specifying the source tag or version when  installing Home-Assistant Core 

* JambulaTV: Add support for using specific versions of Python 3 during  creation of pyenv based virtual environments i.e. Refactor  routines under 'python3_venv_create' in initial and main  functions file 

* JambulaTV: Switch to installing Home-Assistant Core via Python 3 virtual  environments i.e. Refactor the 'homeassistant_pyozw_install'  and 'homeassistant_core_install' routines in initial and main  functions files 

* JambulaTV: Switch to installing Home-Assistant CLI via Python 3 virtual  environments i.e. Refactor the 'homeassistant_cli_install'  routines in initial and main functions files 

* JambulaTV: Add support for dynamically specifying the version of Python 3  package to be installed i.e. Update 'python3_install' routines  in initial install, upgrade and functions files 

* JambulaTV: Add install of 'wheel' package during the creation of pyenv  based virtual environments i.e. Update 'python3_venv_create'  routines in initial and main functions file 

* JambulaTV: Add support for dynamic install, upgrade and runtime usage of  different tags/versions of Home-Assistant core 

* JambulaTV: Add support for destroying Python 3 virtual environments for  previously installed packages  i.e. Add 'python3_venv_destroy' routines to initial and main  functions files 

* JambulaTV: Switch to new method of uninstalling Home-Assistant Core  that was created using Python 3 virtual environments  i.e. Refactor the 'uninstall_homeassistant_core' routines  in initial and main functions files 

* JambulaTV: Support upgrades of Home-Assistant Core using Python 3 virtual  environments i.e. Refactor 'upgrade_homeassistant' routines in  upgrade script 

* JambulaTV: Switch to new method of uninstalling Home-Assistant CLI that  was created using Python 3 virtual environments  i.e. Refactor the 'uninstall_homeassistant_cli' routines in  initial and main functions files 

* JambulaTV: Support use of newly introduced sysconfig defaults file in  CLI tool used to extract variables from the 'secrets.yaml'  file in Home-Assistant Core  i.e. Update 'jambulatv-homeassistant-secrets' 

* JambulaTV: Refactor the Home-Assistant Core configuration routines  i.e. Update 'homeassistant_core_configure' 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Fix minor bugs in un-installation routines for Home-Assistant  Core and CLI 

* JambulaTV: Switch to installing Flexget via Python 3 virtual environments  i.e. Refactor 'flexget_python3_install' routines in initial  and main functions files 

* JambulaTV: Switch to new method of uninstalling Flexget created using  the Python 3 virtual environment  i.e. Refactor the  'uninstall_flexget' routines in initial and main functions  files 

* JambulaTV: Support upgrades of Flexget using Python 3 virtual environments  i.e. Refactor 'upgrade_flexget' routines in the upgrade script 

* JambulaTV: Update install/uninstall routines for Home-Assistant Core in  initial and main functions files 

* JambulaTV: Refactor Flexget upgrade routines in the upgrade script 

* JambulaTV: Refactor Home-Asistant Core upgrade routines in the upgrade  script 

* JambulaTV: Fix the 'VENV_SITE_DIR' variable in Python 3 virtual environment  creation in initial and main functions file 


Changes since v7.5
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where rtorrent process lingers around even after  the command 'systemctl stop rtorrent' has been invoked 

* JambulaTV: Due to security concerns, re-configure rTorrent to use a  local unix domain socket as the endpoint for XMLRPC API  access instead of the localhost address/port endpoint 

* JambulaTV: Include install of xmlrpc, a command line tool used in  accessing the XMLRPC interface to the initial install  and functions script 

* JambulaTV: Due to security concerns, update nginx web server config  file for rtgui to use a local unix domain socket as the  endpoint for XMLRPC API access instead of the localhost  address/port endpoint 

* JambulaTV: Add support for redis, a data structure server used mainly  for caching 

* JambulaTV: Reconfigure NextCloud to use redis server for transactional  file locking.  This is necessary to avoid occasional file  corruption.  Noticed issue with Joplin notes app 

* JambulaTV: Add a Nextcloud based cron job which is used to perform  periodic maintenance operations i.e. Every 15 minutes 

* JambulaTV: Do not show duplicate songs in music playlists created  i.e. Update the systemd unit file that generates the  playlist: jambulatv-radio-playlist.service 

* JambulaTV: Modify command used in generating reminders in the ASR  skills tool i.e. Update jambulatv-asr-skills 

* JambulaTV: Update the tool used to check for the activity and state  of a remote PC i.e. jambulatv-remote-pc-usage-status 

* JambulaTV: Modify Asterisk/FreePBX dialplans to support a brief waiting  period before the PBX answers a phone call i.e. Update the  extensions and global configuration files for both Asterisk  and FreePBX 

* JambulaTV: Re-configure MySQL server to support logging to separate  and smaller files in order to reduce consumption of disk  space by MySQL i.e. Shrink ibdata1 and ib_logfile* files 

* JambulaTV: Remove related cron jobs when uninstalling Nextcloud 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade icinga2 to the latest Github version: r2.13.4-1 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.207 

* JambulaTV: Update icinga2 upgrade routines to include backing up and  restoration of hosts configuration file i.e. hosts.conf 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade prosody XMPP server to the latest version: 0.12.1 

* JambulaTV: Refactor code that generates self-signed SSL certificates  in the initial install and main functions file 

* JambulaTV: Add support for the generation of SSL certificates using a  configuration file 

* JambulaTV: Add file sharing support to Prosody XMPP server i.e. Add  ability to upload files using 'http_file_share' component 

* JambulaTV: Add code to create the OpenSSL configuration template, SSL  certificate and key for prosody server.  Add the generated  certificate to trusted SSL certificates store 

* JambulaTV: Add support for uploads folder to nginx web server.  This is  useful for sharing files within the local network 

* JambulaTV: Add the following port(s) to the list of rules allowed by  the firewall for NoDogSplash or coovachilli if applicable 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade curl to the latest version: 7.86.0 

* JambulaTV: Add support for using a specific bluetooth controller when  performing presence detection using the Icinga2 monitoring  software i.e. Update the icinga2 plugin: check_l2ping 

* JambulaTV: Add the following changes to the weather via scraper tool  i.e. jambulatv-weather-via-scraper 

* JambulaTV: Add new tool named 'jambulatv-search-play-music' which provides  support for searching a given music song and if available  playing it instantly. 

* JambulaTV: Add several TTS generated voice alert sound files that are used  by various automations and scripts in Home-Assistant 

* JambulaTV: Add various sound effects files to the contributed sounds directory 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where Bluez and WiFi devices are intermittently  shown as absent even when present 

* JambulaTV: Add the following On-line radio station(s) to the Internet  radio streamer tool i.e. jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where the streaming of some on-line radio stations  fails due to connection errors 

* JambulaTV: Decrease the volume level used when reading the weather  forecast i.e. Update the weather via scraper tool:  'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.225 

* JambulaTV: Update the system information tool i.e. jambulatv-sysinfo 

* JambulaTV: Modify and update the tvheadend controller tool i.e.  'jambulatv-tvheadend-controller' 

* JambulaTV: Disable debugging in Prosody XMPP server configuration file 


Changes since v7.4
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Add support for adjusting the volume level in the Date/Timetool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-datetime' 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are usedwhen downloading music songs 

* JambulaTV: Add support for voice notification alerts to music downloadtool i.e. update'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Refactor rTorrent install routines in main functions file 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Flexget to the latest development version: 3.3.2 

* JambulaTV: Update the ASR skills tool i.e. 'jambulatv-asr-skills' asfollows: 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are usedwhen reporting power outages 

* JambulaTV: Before promiscuously querying for nearby WiFi devices, bringUP the monitor interface if it is down i.e. Update icinga2plugin: check_tshark 

* JambulaTV: Add 'iwlist' to list of allowed super user commands (sudo)for multimedia user i.e. jambula 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where some podcasts e.g. HASS are not downloadedby 'jambulatv-fetch-podcasts' tool 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.190 

* JambulaTV: Add a new tool named 'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' whichis used to fetch, display, and read weather forecasts fromweather.com, which is a much more reliable source for ourservice area 

* JambulaTV: Add support for Accuweather.com forecasts to our weatherAPI tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Update the Text-2-speech tool 'jambulatv-text2speech' asfollows: 

* JambulaTV:  Add support for weather forecasts provided by weather.com to our ASR skills i.e. Update 'jambulatv-skills' file 

* JambulaTV: Add support for weather forecasts services that use thescraper based tool (e.g. weather.com) to Speech-to-Texttool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-speech2text' 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are usedwhen reading weather forecasts 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are usedwhen the electricity power credits (i.e. UMEME Yaka units)are running low or used-up 

* JambulaTV: Add more TTS generated voice alert sound files that are usedwhen downloading music songs while streaming internet radio 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are usedwhen the Internet data credit is running low or used-up 

* JambulaTV: Add and install google, a Python3 dependency module used by therecently added weather tool i.e. jambulatv-weather-via-scraper 

* JambulaTV: Add geopy Python3 dependency module to the list of commonrequirements installed during initial setup 

* JambulaTV: Update the stream URL(s) for the following on-line basedradio station(s) in the Internet radio streamer tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue with connect to AP tool where USB dongle is seenas absent despite it being actually present 

* JambulaTV: Do not send queued chat messages (Telegram/WhatsApp) whenInternet Data-Saver mode is enabled and Internet statuschanges to UP i.e. Update the Internet/DNS monitoringtool: jambulatv-dns-status-triggers 

* JambulaTV: Change some voice notification sounds used in the musicdownload tool i.e. update'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Update prosody configuration and include info, error anddebug logging in custom directory 

* JambulaTV: Improve reliability of the weather via scraper tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Add support for generating QR codes containing WiFi hotspotcredentials when X display is absent i.e. In console mode 

* JambulaTV: Explicitly specify Text-To-Speech API service to be used byroutines in the ASR skills tool i.e.'jambulatv-asr-skills' 

* JambulaTV: Update the stream URL(s) for the following on-line basedradio station(s) in the Internet radio streamer tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.196 

* JambulaTV: Add support for publishing of alerts to the MQTT brokerwhenever precipitation is observed by the weather viascraper tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Add python-dotenv Python3 dependency module to the listof common requirements installed during initial setup 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 


Changes since v7.3
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Add support for the following features to Home-Assistantand fix a few bugs and issues discovered 

* JambulaTV: Add all options of 'shutdown' to list of allowed superuser commands (sudo) for multimedia user i.e. jambula 

* JambulaTV: Update the Home-Assistant front-end interface and fix bugsas follows: 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade youtube-dl sources to latest version: 2021.12.17 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Android Debug Bridge (ADB) platform tools to thelatest version: 31.0.3-7562133 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade yowsup to the latest Github version: v3.3.0 

* JambulaTV: Update gplaycli sources to the latest Github version 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Flexget to the latest development version: 3.2.9 

* JambulaTV: Fix several issues with the music download tool i.e.Update 'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.170 

* JambulaTV: Due to the recent upgrade of yowsup-cli, change versionof Yowsup in the WhatsApp tool from 3.2.3 to 3.3.0i.e. Update 'jambulatv-whatsapp' 

* JambulaTV: Add new tool named 'jambulatv-cctv-event-via-kodi' whichis used to connect to a remote host running motion CCTVsoftware and generate a snapshot image when motion isdetected.  The image is used by Kodi's 'script.doorbell'plugin to display on the screen 

* JambulaTV: Fix 'skill_headlines' typo in the voice recognition skillstool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-asr-skills' 

* JambulaTV: Restore use of default microphone in the Speech-to-Texttool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-speech2text' 

* JambulaTV: Add new tool named 'jambulatv-fetch-news-via-scraper' whichis used to download an audio summary of the latest globalnews from the BBC (UK) plus local news from Daily Monitor(Uganda) 

* JambulaTV: Update TermFeed_install routines to include a symlink forthe 'feed' program inside binary directory i.e. /usr/bin 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where 'check_internet_connectivity_ping' routinesin main functions do not work as expected i.e. In somecases, failed to alert when there was actual ISP filteringand blocking access of sites like facebook.com as was thethe case in Uganda 

* JambulaTV: Update the weather API tool i.e. jambulatv-weather-api 

* JambulaTV: Update the tool used to check for the activity and stateof a remote PC i.e. jambulatv-remote-pc-usage-status 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where the wireless access point (MiFi) fails todisconnect completely 

* JambulaTV: Do not wait for unlocking of another instance of soundstool if a sound type of 'api' is requested i.e.Update jambulatv-sounds 

* JambulaTV: Fix typo in 'usage_all' routines of speaker volumes tooli.e. Update jambulatv-speaker-volume 

* JambulaTV: Change name of the skill used to call the weather from'skill_weather' to 'skill_weather_currently' inthe Speech-to-Text tool due to upcoming changes in theASR skills tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-speech2text' 

* JambulaTV: Improve the extraction of Home-Assistant variables from'secrets.yaml' file using the command line Interfacei.e. Update 'jambulatv-homeassistant-secrets' tool 

* JambulaTV: Add a new tool named 'jambulatv-datetime' which is usedto announce either the date today or current time andalso supports reading a specified time 

* JambulaTV: Make some minor changes to the newly added fetch news viascraper tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-fetch-news-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Refactor and update the UMEME power outages via scrapertool i.e. jambulatv-umeme-outages-via-scraper 

* JambulaTV: Add and install inflect, a Python3 dependency module usedby the recently added Date/Time announcer tooli.e. jambulatv-datetime 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where rtorrent process lingers around even afterthe command 'systemctl stop' has been invoked 

* JambulaTV: Add new tool named jambulatv-radio-playlist, which is usedto display the current music song playing i.e. now playing 

* JambulaTV: Remove 'now playing' code from Internet radio streamer toolThere's a new standalone tool i.e. jambulatv-radio-playlist 

* JambulaTV: Remove 'now playing' code from the FM radio streamer toolThere's a new standalone tool i.e. jambulatv-radio-playlist 

* JambulaTV: Add support for fetching previously played (outgoing) songtitle to the music download tool i.e. jambulatv-fetch-music 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where specifying 'gain=' as a command option onsome of our tools does not produce the expected result ina situation where multiple arguments in similar form arespecified.  For example, if 'gain=' and 'concatenate=' arecalled in the Text-2-Speech tool, the values returned forthose variables will be incorrect. Correcting it here inthe sounds tool just to be thorough 

* JambulaTV: Update the Text-2-speech tool 'jambulatv-text2speech' asfollows: 

* JambulaTV: Refactor ASR skills tool especially the flash briefing andrelated code routines i.e. Update 'jambulatv-asr-skills' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.178 

* JambulaTV: Add 'homeassistant_skin_customization' routines to initialinstall and functions files. These are mainly for purposesof customizing the web based interface used to log intoour home assistant instance 

* JambulaTV: Update the copyright notice everywhere it is specified inthis project 

* JambulaTV: Add mysql-connector package to the list of commonly usedPython3 modules that are installed during initial setup 

* JambulaTV: Improve and add new features (including fixes) to the smarthome software i.e. Update Home-Assistant automations,scripts, components and several configuration files asfollows: 

* JambulaTV: Add several new TTS generated voice alert sound file(s) tothe project's contributed sounds directory 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade hostapd WiFi server to the latest version of:hostapd v2.11-devel-hostap_2_10-70-gd2e11b7+ 

* JambulaTV: Add support for displaying the genre of the song playingfor online radio stations to the radio playlist tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-radio-playlist' 

* JambulaTV: Add support for downloading previously played music song tothe fetch music tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Fix typo in rTorrent configuration template i.e. Removeextra '.sessions_rtorrent' under session directory inrtorrent.rc file 

* JambulaTV: Change the default Text-to-Speech API service provider backto '2' i.e. Google, as it's not as limiting as IBM Watson 

* JambulaTV: Modify the way the home automation engine i.e. Home-Assistantis started i.e. Update systemd unit: home-assistant.service 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue in date/time tool i.e. jambulatv-datetime wherethe date is not read after the twentieth day of the month 

* JambulaTV: Add support for downloading previously played music songto the ASR skills i.e. Update 'jambulatv-skills' file 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 


Changes since v7.2
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Remove old and unused Python 3 modules in pips directoryi.e. Reduce the size of this repository 

* JambulaTV: Convert voice alert files '1', '5', '6', and '19' from WAVto MP3 format in sounds tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add support for pausing of background music while mobilephone backup tool plays the voice notification alertsi.e. Update 'jambulatv-backup-mobile-phone' 

* JambulaTV: Add the MPD server IP address and port settings plus MPCclient command and options to our global settings file 

* JambulaTV: Use our global settings file to source the MPD server IPaddress/port settings and the MPC client command/optionswhen using the Internet radio streamer tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Use our global settings file to source the MPD server IPaddress/port settings and the MPC client command/optionswhen using the FM radio streamer tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-fm-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Use our global settings file to source the MPD server IPaddress/port settings and the MPC client command/optionswhen using the speaker volumes tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-speaker-volume' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where some mixer levels for ALSA sound systemremain unchanged even after requesting a change duringinitial install and setup 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where locking of current process does not happenfor simultaneous runs of the sounds tool 

* JambulaTV: Add support for pausing of background music while voicenotification alerts are being played by the sounds tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where the startup of Pulseaudio produces errorsdue to recent upgrade and major change in versionIssue caused by deprecation of module-rescue-stream andunsupported module-esound-protocol-tcp in meson builds 

* JambulaTV: Fix several issues with the water supply tool i.e. Updateand refactor 'jambulatv-water-supply' 

* JambulaTV: If the meter reading specified on the command line of thewater supply reading tool is 'unknown', quit processingi.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-reading' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue with hanging of the sounds tool when un-pausingthe MPC player i.e. Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add voice notification support for low disk storagei.e. Alert when running low on hard drive space 

* JambulaTV: Update IBM Watson API endpoint URL in the Text-to-Speechtool necessitated by recent changes by IBM i.e. Update'jambulatv-text2speech' 

* JambulaTV: Add support for updating the date when the water companylast issued an invoice to the water supply reading tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-reading' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where monthly usage is incorrectly calculated bythe water supply tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-supply' 

* JambulaTV: Add initial support for restoring previously archivedandroid data to the mobile phone backup tool 

* JambulaTV: Refactor the uninstall routines for MPV music player ininitial and main functions files i.e. 'uninstall_mpv' 

* JambulaTV: Allow MPV sound player to use pulseaudio sound systemeven when the sink has been suspended so as to avoidhanging of mpv command.  This resolves an issue whereaudio sound from the music player and speaker systemis frequently cut off, leading to missed voice alertsand notifications 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where some Android clients e.g. tablets fail toconnect to the wireless hotspot 

* JambulaTV: Ignore expired SSL certificate when connecting to APIendpoint used in the UMEME power outages via scrapertool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-umeme-outages-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Add support for playing voice notifications and alertsvia Snapcast-based clients e.g smart phones and tabletsin addition to the house speakers 

* JambulaTV: Add voice notification support for presence detectionwhen a user has been away from home for more than 15minutes and over 1 hour 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where speaker volumes tool does not indicatewhen the volume of audio player has been muted 

* JambulaTV: Add voice notification support for presence detectionwhen a user has gone and returned from jogging plusalert when it is time for exercise for specified days 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Improve the extraction of Home-Assistant variables fromsecrets.yaml file using the command line interface i.e.Update 'jambulatv-homeassistant-secrets' tool 

* JambulaTV: Add support for specifying last billed date to the watersupply tool in order to get an accurate number of daysin previous month i.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-supply' 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add voice notification support for daily reminders to input electricity meter readings via the frontend interface 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add support for wireless (WiFi) presence detection usingIcinga2 monitoring software 

* JambulaTV: Add support for controlling non-local (remote) ZoneMinderservers using the CLI based controller tooli.e. Update 'jambulatv-zoneminder-controller' 

* JambulaTV: Add a new tool named 'jambulatv-remote-pc-usage-status'It's purpose is to listen to keyboard and mouse events/presses at a remote PC i.e. Use it to check if a remotecomputer is active or idle.  This could be useful indetecting presence of persons in some environments 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add support for tshark, a command line (CLI) version ofwireshark which is a network protocol analyzer. It allowsfor capture of packet data from a live network.Specifically, we use it here to monitor specified WiFidevices and report when they are seen whether or not theyare connected to an access point 

* JambulaTV: Add WiFi networking support to the mobile phone backuptool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-backup-mobile-phone' 

* JambulaTV: Add newly generated TTS voice alert sound files to thecontributed sounds directory 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.163 

* JambulaTV: Replace the default systemd unit file for DNSMasq withcustomized one i.e. Add 'dnsmasq.service' to projectinit directory. Our version adds a '--test' option todnsmasq command so that syntax checking of theconfiguration file is done before service is started 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where critical dnsmasq service fails to restartwhen activated by the Internet/DNS monitoring tool duringan Internet status change of 'UP' or 'DOWN'Issue is caused by badly formatted DNS blocking list thatis downloaded by the 'jambulatv-dns-status-triggers' tool 

* JambulaTV: Change and rename system hostname to 'server01-JambulaTV' 

* JambulaTV: Configure dnsmasq so that it allocates default system DNSdomains to DHCP server clients i.e. Update 'dnsmasq.conf' 

* JambulaTV: Make Avahi daemon use the default system hostname anddomain-name of 'local'. This fixes minor issues withthe discovery of hosts locally 

* JambulaTV: Add new domain name 'jambula.cc' to the list of project'suniversal domains 

* JambulaTV: Allow access to the time server for not only wired butalso wireless clients i.e. Update 'chrony.conf' andinclude both our 192.168.X.X and 172.16.X.X subnets 

* JambulaTV: Add the following port(s) to the list of rules allowedby the firewall for NoDogSplash or coovachilli ifapplicable: 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 


Changes since v7.1
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Make the 'now playing' code much more reliable especiallywhen reporting the artist and title of locally stored songcurrently playing 

